  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Form X Meanings and Uses",
      "titleArabic": "معاني باب استفعل",
      "content": [
        "Form X (اِسْتَفْعَلَ) typically indicates seeking, asking for, or considering something to have a quality. It can also indicate transformation or reflexive action."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Seeking: اِسْتَغْفَرَ (to seek forgiveness)",
        "Asking: اِسْتَفْهَمَ (to ask for understanding)",
        "Considering: اِسْتَحْسَنَ (to consider good)",
        "Transformation: اِسْتَحْجَرَ (to become like stone)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "اِسْتَغْفَرَ اللهَ", "english": "He sought forgiveness from Allah" },
        { "arabic": "اِسْتَخْدَمَ الْحَاسُوبَ", "english": "He used the computer" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Accusative of Accompaniment (المفعول معه)",
      "titleArabic": "المفعول معه",
      "content": [
        "The maf'ūl ma'ahu (object of accompaniment) indicates what accompanies the action. It follows wāw al-ma'iyya (و of accompaniment) and is always in the accusative."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Follows wāw that means 'along with' or 'during'",
        "Always manṣūb (accusative)",
        "Cannot be conjoined logically with the subject",
        "Common in expressions of walking along something"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "سِرْتُ وَالنَّهْرَ", "english": "I walked along the river" },
        { "arabic": "جَاءَ وَطُلُوعَ الشَّمْسِ", "english": "He came at sunrise" }
      ]
    }
  ],
